==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrinkle
<hw>Wrin"kle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A winkle.</def>
<mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrinkle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wrinkle
<hw>Wrin"kle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wrinkil</ets>, AS.
<ets>wrincle</ets>; akin to OD. <ets>wrinckel</ets>, and prob. to Dan.
<ets>rynke</ets>, Sw. <ets>rynka</ets>, Icel. <ets>hrukka</ets>, OHG.
<ets>runza</ets>, G. <ets>runzel</ets>, L. <ets>ruga</ets>.
<?/<?/<?/<?/.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A small ridge, prominence, or furrow formed by the
shrinking or contraction of any smooth substance; a corrugation; a
crease; a slight fold; <as>as, <ex>wrinkle</ex> in the skin; a
<ex>wrinkle</ex> in cloth.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>wrinkles</xex> in
my brows.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Within I do not find <qex>wrinkles</qex> and used heart, but
unspent youth.</q> <rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>hence, any roughness; unevenness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not the least <qex>wrinkle</qex> to deform the sky.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[Perhaps a different word, and a dim. AS.
<ets>wrenc</ets> a twisting, deceit. Cf. <er>Wrench</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A notion or fancy; a whim; <as>as, to have a
new <ex>wrinkle</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrinkle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wrinkle
<hw>Wrin"kle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Wrinkled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Wrinkling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To contract into furrows and prominences; to make a
wrinkle or wrinkles in; to corrugate; <as>as, <ex>wrinkle</ex> the skin
or the brow</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sport that <xex>wrinkled</xex> Care
derides.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her <qex>wrinkled</qex> form in black and white arrayed.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to make rough or uneven in any way.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A keen north wind that, blowing dry,⟦br⟧
<qex>Wrinkled</qex> the face of deluge, as decayed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then danced we on the <qex>wrinkled</qex> sand.</q>
<rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To wrinkle at</b></col>, <cd>to sneer at.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Marston.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrinkle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Wrinkle
<hw>Wrin"kle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To shrink into furrows and
ridges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrinkly</ent>⟦br⟧
